In recent months, Vodacom and MTN have cut the prices of their large contract data bundles – offering subscribers up to 80GB per month. Vodacom’s “SIM-only Big Data deals” offer subscribers between 10GB and 60GB of data per month, with prices ranging between R179 and R379. MTN is offering between 8GB and 80GB per month on its “Double your data” subscriptions, with prices ranging between R89 and R499 per month. The table below provides an overview of how Vodacom and MTN’s prices compare on these contract data bundles.  